\subsection{SLRP.6}
=TEX
=SML
=DUMP mdt017f.grm.txt
(* Grammar for a Pocket Calculator with « meaning addition and tab meaning multiplication! *)
	E	=	E, `«`, T				(add x1 x3)
		|	T 				(fetch x1);

	T	=	T, `	`, F			(mul x1 x3)
		|	F				(fetch x1);

	F	=	`(`, E, `)`			(fetch x2)
		|	Num				(conv x1);
=TEX
We use the following datatype for the lexical classes here:
=SML
